---
// Two clear pathways for how Leigh-Ann can work with you.
---

<section id="two-paths" class="bg-ink text-paper py-16 md:py-24 relative overflow-hidden">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-12 md:mb-16" data-reveal>
      <p class="small-caps text-copper mb-5">Chapter One</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-paper leading-[0.95]">
        Two ways to <span class="italic font-display-italic">work with me</span>.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-paper/65 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">
        A seasoned senior EA can fit either shape of need. Choose the one that matches your org, or reach out to talk about a hybrid.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 md:gap-12">
      <!-- Path 1: Part-time / Full-time -->
      <article class="relative border border-paper/15 rounded-sm p-8 md:p-10 hover:border-copper/50 transition-colors" data-reveal>
        <div class="absolute -top-3 left-8 bg-ink px-3">
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-copper">Path 01</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-paper leading-tight mb-6">
          Hire me as your<br/>
          <span class="italic font-display-italic text-copper">embedded</span> EA.
        </h3>
        <p class="text-paper/70 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          For CEOs and founders who want a senior EA fully embedded with their executive office. Part-time (20 to 30 hours) or full-time.
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-10">
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-copper mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0">01</span>
            <span class="text-paper/85 text-sm leading-relaxed">Calendar and correspondence for one to three execs</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-copper mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0">02</span>
            <span class="text-paper/85 text-sm leading-relaxed">Board, committee, and investor-relations coordination</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-copper mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0">03</span>
            <span class="text-paper/85 text-sm leading-relaxed">Team leadership, EA onboarding, and process documentation</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-copper mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0">04</span>
            <span class="text-paper/85 text-sm leading-relaxed">AI-fluent daily workflow (Claude, Perplexity, Salesforce CPA)</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="pt-6 border-t border-paper/10">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-4">
            <span class="small-caps text-paper/40">Target compensation</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-paper tabular">$120K to $165K base</span>
          </div>
          <a
            href="#contact"
            class="group inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-copper text-sm font-medium hover:gap-3 transition-all"
          >
            <span>Reach out about full-time</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Path 2: Fractional -->
      <article class="relative bg-paper text-ink rounded-sm p-8 md:p-10 shadow-2xl" data-reveal>
        <div class="absolute -top-3 left-8 bg-paper px-3">
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-copper">Path 02</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-ink leading-tight mb-6">
          Engage me<br/>
          <span class="italic font-display-italic text-copper">fractionally</span>.
        </h3>
        <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-8">
          For founders scaling through a specific chapter without the budget or need for a full-time senior EA. Outcome-based engagements, not hourly.
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-10">
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-copper mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0">01</span>
            <span class="text-ink-soft text-sm leading-relaxed">Board governance setup and quarterly cadence</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-copper mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0">02</span>
            <span class="text-ink-soft text-sm leading-relaxed">Earnings-call prep system for newly public or pre-IPO</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-copper mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0">03</span>
            <span class="text-ink-soft text-sm leading-relaxed">EA function build-out with onboarding frameworks</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-copper mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0">04</span>
            <span class="text-ink-soft text-sm leading-relaxed">Investor-relations operations and stakeholder systems</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="pt-6 border-t border-rule">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-4">
            <span class="small-caps text-ink-muted">Engagement range</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-ink tabular">$3K to $15K per project</span>
          </div>
          <a
            href="#services"
            class="group inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-copper text-sm font-medium hover:gap-3 transition-all"
          >
            <span>See fractional packages</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
